GOVINFO OVERVIEW
==============================================================================

GovInfo provides official publications from all three branches of the Federal
Government, including oversight reports, audits, investigations, hearings,
court opinions, and regulatory documents.

AVAILABLE COLLECTIONS (choose 1-3 most relevant):

**Oversight & Audits:**
- GAOREPORTS: GAO (Government Accountability Office) audits, investigations, testimonies
  Use for: Government waste, fraud, program effectiveness, agency oversight
  Example: "GAO report on defense contracting waste"

**Congressional Documents:**
- CRPT: Congressional committee reports (House/Senate committee findings)
  Use for: Investigation reports, policy recommendations, oversight findings
  Example: "Senate Armed Services Committee report on F-35 program"

- CHRG: Congressional hearing transcripts
  Use for: Testimony, Q&A sessions, expert witnesses
  Example: "Hearing on cybersecurity threats to critical infrastructure"

- CREC: Congressional Record (daily proceedings, floor speeches)
  Use for: Statements, debates, legislative history
  Example: "Senator's speech on defense authorization bill"

**Legal & Regulatory:**
- USCOURTS: Federal court opinions (appellate, district, bankruptcy)
  Use for: Legal precedents, contractor lawsuits, fraud cases
  Example: "Court opinion on False Claims Act case against Lockheed"

- CFR: Code of Federal Regulations
  Use for: Federal regulations, compliance requirements
  Example: "FAR regulations on government contracting"

- PLAW: Public and Private Laws (enacted legislation)
  Use for: Final law text, legislative intent
  Example: "National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2024"

**Other:**
- CDIR: Congressional Directory (member biographies, committees)
- BILLS/BILLSTATUS: Congressional bills (NOTE: Use Congress.gov integration instead for bills)

